headline.main: 5 British-U.S. Ambulances to Tour Nation To Raise Funds for R.A.F. Rescue Planes

lead_paragraph: Five ambulances of the British-American Ambulance Corps, 420 Lexington Avenue, which were formally named the "Thumbs Up Cavalcade," will leave today for San Francisco on a tour to raise funds for medical supplies and airplane ambulances for the R.A.F. and Great Britain's Allies.
